derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English: via French électeur from Latin elector, from the verb eligere (see elect)

entry.def: An elector is a person who has the right to vote in an election.
An elector is a member of the electoral college. People vote for electors in each state to represent them in the presidential elections.

means.word_mean: 1. a citizen who has a legal right to vote
